        <abstract> 
<p>The translation of Humboldt’s <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi> [<hi rend="italic">Cosmos</hi> (1846–58)] is delayed.</p> 
            <p>Gives instances of peculiar genera with several good species in very small islands. Scarcity of insects on islands.</p>
            <p>JDH cannot prove that there is much hybridising, but does not see why there should not be. "Bother variation, development &amp; all such subjects, it is reasoning in a circle I believe after all."</p>
        </abstract>
